The helper method to add the GlobalMenuItemBean contentss to MDS. The underlying API will return a boolean value: true if the addEntry completes successfully. false if the addEntry does not complete successfully the exception thrown will explain why the action was not successful. It is up to the calling code to catch and take the appropriate action for the error.

The helper method used to delete an entry that has been added as part of a customization. The calling code should have already validated that menu item is one added as part of a customization by checking the isBaseNode method. If the item is a base node the calling code should do a updateEntry setting the rendered flag to false.
